The retail price of petrol (93 ULP & LRP) will go down by R1.22 per litre in January, the Department of Energy announced on Friday. It will come into effect on Wednesday January 2, 2019. Petrol (95 ULP & LRP) will decrease by R1.23 per litre, while diesel (0.05% sulphur) will go down by R1.53 per litre and diesel (0.005% sulphur) will decrease by R1.55 per litre. The wholesale price of illuminating paraffin will decrease by R1.23.     The fuel prices schedule for the different zones will be published on Monday, 31 December 2018.  https://www.fin24.com/Economy/energy-department-confirms-huge-fuel-price-drop-for-january-20181228